<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="256" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,271,1134]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,381,407]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet honors Dr. Edmund Jarzembowski to acknowledge his contribution to the study of extinct 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[317,400,454,480]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="2" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="class">Insecta</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="256" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,271,1134]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,312,489,515]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tiny round wing with pterostigma, Rs base almost transverse, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[432,440,544,558]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">5</subScript>
longer than distal section of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[155,181,580,594]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">4+5</subScript>
, anal lobe reduced.
</paragraph>
